One of the most important features that every user of the YouTube video platform needs is the feature to download videos from the platform, which was not available in the past and used to depend on third applications and software, but YouTube is currently working on testing a new feature that will enable That is in a legal way.


And Android Police said the new beta feature has been spotted for YouTube Premium subscribers in India and France, and appears to be widely available elsewhere. on the toolbar under the title.



YouTube said about the topic on its official website: "Click the Download button while watching a video or click the three-dot menu while browsing. Note: This is only available on computers running the latest versions of Chrome, Edge or Opera browsers."



Android Police points out that in the settings menu, the user can choose to download in a different quality with a maximum resolution of 1080p, or delete all local downloads from the browser cache with a single button.